The marked right triangle has a hypotenuse of $\sqrt{6^2+8^2}=10$, which makes the other (congruent) triangle a right triangle as well. The area of the entire figure is then the area of the rectangle added to the area of the two right triangles, or $12\cdot8+2\left(\frac{6\cdot8}{2}\right)=\boxed{144}$ square inches.

